{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6ac657ff-5de5-4f39-9e2d-dde2d536145d","content":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me migrate. Key xUnit v3 changes: test projects become executables, the `xunit.v3` package replaces `xunit` + runner + test SDK.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_012RFcyN9xcawmt7KQcfxhXg","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bce8895915b445c099945e240181ba1d/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>\n    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"18.3.0\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit\" Version=\"2.9.3\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"2.8.2\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>","new_str":"<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>\n    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>\n    <IsPackable>false</IsPackable>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"xunit.v3\" Version=\"1.1.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-bce8895915b445c099945e240181ba1d/TestProject.csproj."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_019hEGobBzr9ck2w7WgMvKAq","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-bce8895915b445c099945e240181ba1d/global.json","old_str":"{\n  \"test\": {\n    \"runner\": \"VSTest\"\n  }\n}","new_str":"{\n  \"test\": {\n    \"runner\": \"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\"\n  }\n}"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-bce8895915b445c099945e240181ba1d/global.json."}],"interactionId":"1eff85f0-b6ae-427a-a97b-c6b7ae8f2ba1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I understand the current setup. Let me migrate from xUnit v2 to xUnit v3. Key changes needed:\n\n1. **TestProject.csproj**:\n   - Replace `xunit` (v2) with `xunit.v3` (v3)\n   - Remove `xunit.runner.visualstudio` (v2 runner) — xUnit v3 uses `xunit.runner.visualstudio.v3` or the built-in runner\n   - Actually, in xUnit v3, the project becomes an executable (Exe) rather than a library\n   - Remove `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — not needed for xUnit v3 (it has its own entry point)\n   - Change `OutputType` to `Exe` since xUnit v3 test projects are executables\n\n2. **CalculatorTests.cs**: The test attributes like `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` remain the same, and assertions like `Assert.Equal` should continue to work without changes.\n\nNow I'm looking more carefully at the xUnit v3 migration specifics. The key differences are that the package becomes `xunit.v3` instead of `xunit`, the project type switches to an executable, and the `xunit.v3` package automatically generates an entry point so I don't need `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` or `xunit.runner.visualstudio`. Looking at the test method signatures, `[Fact]` and `[Theory]` attributes work similarly in v3, though `[Fact]` methods need to return `void` or `Task`. For the project file itself, I need to set `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`, swap `xunit` for `xunit.v3`, and remove both `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and `xunit.runner.visualstudio`. The target framework needs to be at least `net6.0` since v3 requires .NET 6 or higher.\n\nFor the global.json configuration, xUnit v3 uses Microsoft Testing Platform by default instead of VSTest, so I should either remove the test runner specification or update it to reflect the new platform—though I'm uncertain about the exact global.json format for this change. I need to check NuGet for the actual latest version of xunit.v3 and then plan out the migration steps—updating the project file to use Exe output type and swapping in the new package references.","outputTokens":2193,"requestId":"0845:E43FA:DE6947:100934E:69EAC873"},"id":"256d7261-fdcf-4e7